.TH TGLFS-INSPECT 1 "March 2026" "tglfs 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tglfs-inspect \- inspect file-card metadata, chunk references, and current-vs-legacy format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tglfs inspect
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIufid\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Shows the file-card metadata, checks whether each referenced chunk message exists and is a Telegram document, and probes whether the file restores with the current or legacy download pipeline.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --peer <peer>
Peer to inspect instead of Saved Messages.
.TP
.B --password <password>
Password to use for current-vs-legacy probing.
.TP
.B --password-env [name]
Read the probe password from an environment variable. If no name is provided, the command uses
.B TGLFS_INSPECT_PASSWORD.
.TP
.B --password-stdin
Read the probe password from standard input.
.TP
.B --json
Emit machine-readable JSON.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TGLFS_INSPECT_PASSWORD
Default environment variable for the probe password.
